    <h1 class="heading1">Psychiatry Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Psychiatry Department is dedicated to providing compassionate and comprehensive mental health care. Led by a team of experienced psychiatrists, psychologists, social workers, and psychiatric nurses, we offer a range of services to diagnose, treat, and support individuals with mental health disorders, helping them achieve optimal mental well-being and quality of life.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Psychiatric Evaluation and Diagnosis</h4>
            <p>We provide comprehensive psychiatric evaluations to assess mental health symptoms, determine diagnosis, and develop personalized treatment plans. Our team of psychiatrists conducts thorough assessments, considering biological, psychological, and social factors contributing to mental health conditions, to provide accurate diagnosis and effective treatment recommendations.</p>

            <h4>Medication Management</h4>
            <p>Our psychiatrists offer medication management services to prescribe and monitor psychotropic medications for the treatment of mental health disorders. We work closely with patients to determine the most appropriate medication regimen based on their symptoms, preferences, and medical history, ensuring safe and effective treatment outcomes.</p>

            <h4>Psychotherapy</h4>
            <p>We provide various forms of psychotherapy to help individuals explore thoughts, feelings, and behaviors, develop coping strategies, and improve overall mental well-being. Our therapists offer evidence-based psychotherapeutic approaches, such as cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), dialectical behavior therapy (DBT), interpersonal therapy (IPT), and psychodynamic therapy, tailored to meet the unique needs of each patient.</p>

            <h4>Group Therapy</h4>
            <p>Group therapy sessions offer a supportive and therapeutic environment for individuals to connect with others facing similar challenges, share experiences, and learn from one another. Our group therapy programs cover a range of topics, including stress management, anger management, substance abuse recovery, grief and loss, and interpersonal skills development, providing additional support and encouragement to our patients.</p>

            <h4>Family Therapy and Support</h4>
            <p>We recognize the importance of involving family members and loved ones in the treatment process, especially for individuals with mental health disorders. Our psychiatrists and therapists offer family therapy sessions to improve communication, resolve conflicts, and strengthen relationships, empowering families to provide essential support and participate in the recovery journey.</p>

            <h4>Community Outreach and Education</h4>
            <p>Our Psychiatry Department is committed to raising awareness about mental health and reducing stigma in the community. We conduct educational workshops, seminars, and outreach programs to promote mental health awareness, provide resources, and facilitate access to mental health services for individuals and families in need.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
